                            <comment id="12706691" author="streamy" created="Thu, 7 May 2009 01:41:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just posting in case anyone wanted to take a look.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lots of changes to KeyValue and dependencies.  I moved things away from fam:qf notation as much as I could, it&apos;s going to require finishing up everything else like gets() before we can move all the way.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Includes some modifications to the KV unit test.  Patch passes tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12706721" author="stack" created="Thu, 7 May 2009 05:17:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this in wrong place in HConstants?  Seems after when it should be before:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//
&lt;/span&gt;+  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// New stuff.  Making a slow transition.
&lt;/span&gt;+  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//
&lt;/span&gt;+  
+
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Your style is a little odd.  In below your (lack-of) spacing is different from rest of hbase/hadoop style.  You do this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.bytes = createByteArray(row,0,rlength,column,0,clength,
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then in line above the one above, you put spaces around everything.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is another (unreadable) example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;(row,0,row==&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;?0:row.length,family,0,family==&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;?0:family.length,
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add class javadoc to SplitKeyValue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is this a regression?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
-        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; kv.matchingColumnNoDelimiter(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.col, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.familylength);
+        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; kv.matchingColumnNoDelimiter(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.col);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The passed column has a delimiter or not?  Doesn&apos;t? Need to know where its offset is?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This belongs in KV I think rather than Bytes.... no need of polluting Bytes with KV and column stuff: parseColumn&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Otherwise, patch looks great.  Passes tests?&lt;/p&gt;


</comment>
                            <comment id="12706942" author="streamy" created="Thu, 7 May 2009 15:43:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review, stack.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unit test passes, there are other parts of my code that don&apos;t compile yet so a little longer before I can run full tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Agree on all other notes, will take care of them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
